.TH "stm32_spi_can_dma" 9 "stm32_spi_can_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stm32_spi_can_dma \- Determine if the transfer is eligible for DMA use
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" stm32_spi_can_dma
.BI "(struct spi_master *master "  ","
.BI "struct spi_device *spi_dev "  ","
.BI "struct spi_transfer *transfer "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "master" 12
controller master interface
.IP "spi_dev" 12
pointer to the spi device
.IP "transfer" 12
pointer to spi transfer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If driver has fifo and the current transfer size is greater than fifo size,
use DMA. Otherwise use DMA for transfer longer than defined DMA min bytes.
